<Author>jeanrelle
<Content>Lovely hotel - shame about the beds Stayed 4 nights at NH Master in Barcelona. Was very new looking and reception were very pleasant and helpful. Some staff had limited english. The room was very modern - had a window that opened onto a central light area with no views at all. Did not worry us. Airconditioning was hard to work out, so spent a few nights quite hot. The worse was the bed situation - as they were singles pushed together. With no clasp to keep the beds together it was not very romantic! I will email and complain to the NH group (as there are many hotels) but will want to double check this next time. Towels and linen were all clean and new - would recommend highly but watch for the bed situation. Location was ok...although next time I would pick a hotel near the metro Jaume - as we walked down that way for all the better restaurants. 
