<Author>Peter11435
<Content>Nice Stay, Shame About The Map! In our experience the NH chaim is one that you can trust.The hotels are always clean and effecient and the complimentary toiletries are a nice touch too.That said the hotel didn't really get off to a good start with us.First of all the map on the hotel's e-mailed confirmation to us gave the impression that it was a mere 500 metres from the main railway station - that was not the case and caused a degree of anxiety for my wife and I. We ended up getting a 5 minute taxi ride.In the light of day the hotel proved to be a five minute walk from the metro or around the corner from a bus stop.By the time we arrived (9:30 pm), both the hotel bar and resturant had closed, so we had to resort to room service for something to eat as we were both exhausted by then.From then on however, the hotel performed ok. The room was spacious and the bathroom was lovely, although judging by our experience it must be siad that the walls are paper thin!We also used their laundry service, and although expensive, they did a very good job and presented the clothes beautifully. 
