<Author>AmFl
<Content>I just don't get it.... We stayed here for one night in Oct....were supposed to stay for more, but upon checking in, they could not give us a non-smoking room eventhough we had requested it months before. We found the front desk staff to be very un-friendly and the room not very comforatable. The walls were very thin and we could hear the people in the room next to us clearly - it was as though they were in the room with us. While the hallways and the room seemed as though they had been renovated, the bathroom was in need of some attention. Fixtures were old and not very clean. Also, we had a drainage pipe in our room beside the bed and you could constantly hear water going through it. As for the location, we found that it was a bit off the beaten path for us. The day we checked in, we walked down to Las Ramblas and it was about a 20 minute walk. Needless, to say, we checked out the next day and moved to a different hotel. I should also mention that although the hotel says on its site that they have WiFi, it is not free and the interent in the lobby is also not free. 
